# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is managed by the user. However, for a specific project, it is recommended to include them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1185, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in cases where the dependencies are not well-defined, it might be better to ignore it.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

